It use to be so much better. Small neighborhood Koren restaurant with a decent menu. Over the years as the restaurant has renovated and their menu has expanded, unfortunately, their food—taste and quality—has gotten worse. I think the intention and focus is to serve really young diners (teens on dates) and the Columbia Community—the rest of us can eat elsewhere. The prices aren't that affordable, service is spotty, but it's a place to sit and get something quick.  They'll also give you a 10% discount for settling with cash.  My advice, have patience when you order;  be prepared  to repeat everything you say at least 3 times.  Stick to the menu, no extra anything,  no deviations or substitutions—you won't get it even if they take your requests upon ordering. We stopped doing delivery years ago (it seemed to take years to have your food delivered) and only do takeout now. Also, if you order through Seemless, call the restaurant to confirm your order and delivery time about 5 min after placing your order. We do better calling and ordering directly. Cross your fingers that you got the best chef on his/her best day!  Update:  well, I can say the pandemic has affected the quality of the food at KoKo Wings. Guess what, they have gotten even worse.  GET YOUR RECEIPT they will deny that it's their food if you don't have a receipt.

Great Korean fried chicken in uptown! It's worth every bite and the spicy is actually spicy. The shell of a crust is holding back all the juices so be careful. The meat is so tender and just flavorful. I dare you to not want to lick your fingers clean

We tried the soy garlic chicken strips which were tiny yet adequate. We also had the golbak some spicy minced chicken plate with gochujang. The dish was appropriate but good lord take anything mozzarella off your menus. The restaurant was understaffed, the heat was not working, and the server although cordial, had no clue what they were doing.

Best korean wings.  Perfectly crispy, flavor to the bone.  Make sure to get the sweet potato fries.
I'm in love with the KOKO!
Great Korean fried chicken and accompanying dishes.  Small but clean and comfortable

The best Korean style fried chicken I've ever had. It is ironic that, as a Korean who lived in Korea for 30+ yrs, I found the best Korean style fried chicken in Manhattan. The chicken is available in two types of sauce:spicy or non-spicy. Both sauces are awesome, so I usually order half-and-half, e.g., 3  non-spicy and 3 spicy for 6-piece wings. If you live far away (perhaps several blocks away) where they can't deliver, you can order by phone and pick up. The restaurant has clean and nice interior with several tables. Also, the friendly and nice staff is a bonus.
Spicy wings and sweet potato fries. My favorite junk food place around Columbia. Whoever doesn't love their wings have issues I think

My new favorite restaurant in the neighborhood!  Staff are lovely people, the restaurant is clean and well laid out, and most importantly for a restaurant, the food is fantastic!  Love the chicken, especially the spicy blend, and the french fries are a must!  It's pretty cheap for the amount of food you get, too.  My wife and I can share a single order of strips, whatever side, and an order of fries, and we're both stuffed before the food is gone!  You can get this at very few other restaurants in the area for under $20 (really it's only possible at fast food - yuck), but it is possible at Koko Wings.  Do yourself a favor and go get yourself some chicken!
Awesome wings!

The hot & spicy chicken wing flavor is amazing!! Kimchi slaw amazing!! Sweet potato fries Amazing! Fast delivery, fairly priced. Only downfall was that we wished the wings had more meat on them.  They r really small wings.
My favorite chicken place!!! Great!!

New (opened spring 2014) Korean fried chicken in Morningside! Right across Broadway is Kentucky fried chicken so theres something to kill every kind of KFC killing.  The sweet potato fries are only okay IMO. Battered and not gluten-free; with cinnamon sugar and a hint of spice. Takoyaki also was only alright.  The wings are good though! Soy garlic is tasty even for kids (not spicy).  They do takeout but brush up on your Korean before calling in your order.
Delicious korean style chicken-
